source_code_description: Clinical: Diagnosis made before death without (2-7)
Clinical investigation: Includes all diagnostic techniques without a tissue diagnosis
Specific tumour markers: Includes biochemical and/or immunological markers which are site specific

Cytology: Examination of cells whether from a primary or secondary site, including fluids aspirated using endoscopes or needles. Also including microscopic examination of peripheral blood films and trephine bone marrow aspirates
Histology of a metastases: Includes autopsy specimens
Histology of a primary tumour: Includes all cutting and bone marrow biopsies. Also includes autopsy specimens of a primary tumour
